# Smart Contracts

ExactPay uses smart contracts to automate critical parts of the payment lifecycle while ensuring transparency and deterministic execution.

## Planned Contract Modules

### Identity Contract
- Stores reusable identity credentials.
- Validates Zero-Knowledge verification proofs.
- Eliminates repeated identity verification.

### Payment Contract
- Initiates cross-border payment requests.
- Records payment transactions.
- Links sender and recipient.

### Settlement Contract
- Calculates the final recipient amount.
- Locks settlement parameters before execution.
- Ensures financial certainty.

### Financial Profile Contract
- Maintains a verifiable history of successful transfers.
- Supports future lending and insurance eligibility.

---

These contracts represent the planned architecture for the ExactPay platform and will be implemented as the project evolves.
